===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|pece}}, {{m|enm|peas}}, {{m|enm|pees}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|pais||peace}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|pāx||peace}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*paḱ-||to fasten, stick, place}}, related to {{etyl|la|-}} {{m|la|pacīscor||agree, stipulate}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{m|la|pangō||fasten, fix}}; see {{l|en|pact}}. Displaced native {{etyl|enm|-}} {{m|enm|frith}}, {{m|enm|frede||peace}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|friþ}}, {{m|ang|frēod||peace}}), {{etyl|enm|-}} {{m|enm|sib|sib, sibbe|peace}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|sibb||peace, kinship}}), {{etyl|enm|-}} {{m|enm|grith||peace, security}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|griþ}} and {{etyl|non|-}} {{m|non|grið}}), {{etyl|enm|-}} {{m|enm|saught|saht, saught|peace, reconciliation}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|seht}}, {{m|ang|sæht||peace, pact, agreement}}).

